      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Zxpghfs9NJXf"
      },
      "source": [
        "The dataset is from an ongoing cardiovascular study on residents of the town of Framingham,\n",
        "Massachusetts.\n",
        "\n",
        "The classification goal is to predict whether the patient has a 10-year risk of\n",
        "future coronary heart disease (CHD). \n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset provides the patients’ information. It includes\n",
        "over 4,000 records and 15 attributes.\n",
        "Variables\n",
        "Each attribute is a potential risk factor. There are both demographic, behavioral, and medical risk\n",
        "factors.\n",
        "\n",
        "# **Data Description**\n",
        "### **Demographic:**\n",
        "* Sex: male or female(\"M\" or \"F\")\n",
        "* Age: Age of the patient;(Continuous - Although the recorded ages have been truncated to whole numbers, the concept of age is continuous)\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Behavioral**\n",
        "* is_smoking: whether or not the patient is a current smoker (\"YES\" or \"NO\")\n",
        "* Cigs Per Day: the number of cigarettes that the person smoked on average in one day.(can be\n",
        "considered continuous as one can have any number of cigarettes, even half a cigarette.)\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Medical( history)**\n",
        "* BP Meds: whether or not the patient was on blood pressure medication (Nominal)\n",
        "* Prevalent Stroke: whether or not the patient had previously had a stroke (Nominal)\n",
        "* Prevalent Hyp: whether or not the patient was hypertensive (Nominal)\n",
        "* Diabetes: whether or not the patient had diabetes (Nominal)\n",
        "Medical(current)\n",
        "* Tot Chol: total cholesterol level (Continuous)\n",
        "* Sys BP: systolic blood pressure (Continuous)\n",
        "* Dia BP: diastolic blood pressure (Continuous)\n",
        "* BMI: Body Mass Index (Continuous)\n",
        "* Heart Rate: heart rate (Continuous - In medical research, variables such as heart rate though in\n",
        "fact discrete, yet are considered continuous because of large number of possible values.)\n",
        "* Glucose: glucose level (Continuous)\n",
        "Predict variable (desired target)\n",
        "* 10-year risk of coronary heart disease CHD(binary: “1”, means “Yes”, “0” means “No”) -\n",
        "DV"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "qmpG9TGrNF1r"

      "source": [
        "**Is Heart rate is responsible for CHD ??**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jGqBKFBE4lL9"
      },
      "source": [
        "def heartRate_data(row):\n",
        "    if row['heartRate'] <= 59:\n",
        "        value = 'Low'\n",
        "    elif row['heartRate'] < 100:\n",
        "        value = 'Normal'\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        value = \"High\"\n",
        "    \n",
        "    return value"
      ],
      "execution_count": 73,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NFflJ-jQ4x7F"
      },
      "source": [
        "cvs_df['heartRateLabel'] = cvs_df.apply(heartRate_data, axis = 1)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 74,
      "outputs": []
    },

      "metadata": {
        "id": "Qe634Ct2Z6_Y"
      },
      "source": [
        "#2. Model Building\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ITZG75G1Z2av"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Feature engineering"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MLHO21cWbiMQ"
      },
      "source": [
        "Systolic and Diastolic blood pressure has a high correlation that can be commonly classified into hypertension."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GGSIcx1USJDU"
      },
      "source": [
        "def blood_presure_classification(SysBP, DiaBP):\n",
        "  if (SysBP < 90) or (DiaBP < 60):\n",
        "    return 0 # 'Hypotension'\n",
        "  if (SysBP < 120) and (DiaBP < 80):\n",
        "    return 1 # 'Optimal'\n",
        "  if (SysBP < 130) or (DiaBP < 86):\n",
        "    return 2 # 'Normal'\n",
        "  if (SysBP < 140) or (DiaBP < 90):\n",
        "    return 3 # 'PreHypertensive'\n",
        "  if (SysBP > 140) and (DiaBP < 90):\n",
        "    return 4 # 'IsolatedSystolicHypertension'\n",
        "  if (SysBP < 160) or (DiaBP < 100):\n",
        "    return 5 # 'GradeI'\n",
        "  if (SysBP < 180) or (DiaBP < 110):\n",
        "    return 6 # 'GradeII'\n",
        "  return 7 # 'GradeIII'"
      ],
      "execution_count": 85,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "JCSJtErk2WSc",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 237
        },
        "outputId": "dbab20b3-d5d0-4452-8671-61a625bf78d5"
      },
      "source": [
        "cvs_df['Hypertension'] = cvs_df.apply(lambda x: blood_presure_classification(x['sysBP'],x['diaBP']),axis=1)\n",
        "cvs_df.head()"
      ],
      "execution_count": 86,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7IIX991RjTnl"
      },
      "source": [
        "Blood glucose levels can be used to classify the severity of Diabetes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Qx8cGPumjscq"
      },
      "source": [
        "def diabetes_grade(glucose):\n",
        "  if glucose < 100:\n",
        "    return 1 # 'Normal'\n",
        "  if glucose < 125:\n",
        "    return 2 # 'Prediabetic'\n",
        "  if glucose < 200:\n",
        "    return 3 # 'Mild'\n",
        "  if glucose < 400:\n",
        "    return 4 # 'Moderate'\n",
        "  return 5 # 'Severe'    "
      ],
      "execution_count": 87,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 257
        },
        "id": "yEMBSFOjlcbY",
        "outputId": "a11c0a72-7f10-41f1-88b7-99816927c200"
      },
      "source": [
        "cvs_df['Diabetes'] = cvs_df['glucose'].apply(lambda x: diabetes_grade(x))\n",
        "cvs_df.head()"

      "source": [
        "The absolute number of cigarettes per day is not much useful variable because the stiffness of blood vessels increases as the number of cigarettes consumed per day increases. So new feature containing log-transformed value could be more useful."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 257
        },
        "id": "AtaRXooCnfUG",
        "outputId": "eb08a7d4-4168-4dd3-a579-a484d290993d"
      },
      "source": [
        "cvs_df['SmokingFactor'] = cvs_df['cigsPerDay'].apply(lambda x: 0 if x < 1 else np.log(x))\n",

      "source": [
        "X = cvs_df[independent_variable].values\n",
        "y = cvs_df[dependent_variable].values"
      ],
      "execution_count": 98,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cTk0Q0Bc0d4R"
      },
      "source": [
        "Let's Resample the dataset to over come this imbalance.\n",
        "We will apply SMOTE (Synthetic Minority Oversampling Technique) to resample the data. It works by randomly picking a point from the minority class and computing the k-nearest neighbors for this point. The synthetic points are added between the chosen point and its neighbors."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "3EP57G_X0iAX",
        "outputId": "400f2892-de6c-459c-8ef8-3118b8ff42dc"
      },
      "source": [
        "# the numbers before SMOTE\n",
        "num_before = dict(Counter(y))\n",
        "\n",
        "#perform SMOTE\n",
        "\n",
        "# define pipeline\n",
        "under = RandomUnderSampler(sampling_strategy=0.8)\n",
        "over = SMOTE(sampling_strategy=0.8)\n",
        "steps = [('o', over), ('u', under)]\n",
        "pipeline = Pipeline(steps=steps)\n",
        "\n",
        "# transform the dataset\n",
        "X_smote, y_smote = pipeline.fit_resample(X, y)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "#the numbers after SMOTE\n",
        "num_after =dict(Counter(y_smote))\n",
        "print(num_before, num_after)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 99,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "{0: 2483, 1: 444} {0: 2482, 1: 1986}\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2EUBTlShonkd"
      },
      "source": [
        "# split the data\n",
        "X_train,X_test,y_train,y_test = train_test_split(X_smote,y_smote,test_size=.2)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 100,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tXQe3qdCV4ui"

        "\n",

        "\n",

        "X_test = pd.DataFrame(X_test_scaled)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 101,

      "source": [
        "## **Knn**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CrWKqZHdz_hw"
      },
      "source": [
        "# calculate accuracy score for first 10 neighbors\n",
        "# Setup arrays to store training and test accuracies\n",
        "neighbors = 10\n",
        "train_accuracy = np.empty(neighbors)\n",
        "test_accuracy = np.empty(neighbors)\n",
        "\n",
        "for i in range(1, neighbors + 1):\n",
        "    # Setup a knn classifier with k neighbors\n",
        "    knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=i)\n",
        "    # Fit the model\n",
        "    knn.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "    # Compute accuracy on the training set\n",
        "    train_accuracy[i - 1] = knn.score(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "    # Compute accuracy on the test set\n",
        "    test_accuracy[i - 1] = knn.score(X_test, y_test) "
      ],
      "execution_count": 102,
      "outputs": []
    },
